First, connect `useStream` to your human-in-the-loop agent. When the graph hits an interrupt, the hook exposes the pending payload on `stream.interrupt`. Render an approval card while that value is set, then resume the run with `stream.submit(null, { command: { resume: response } })` after the user approves, rejects, or edits the action.

