You can extract and join reasoning blocks from an `AIMessage` using the `extractBlocks` function, as shown in [S1](#s1). This function filters the `contentBlocks` array by type to separate reasoning from text, and then joins the reasoning blocks together.

Here is the code snippet from [S1](#s1):
```ts
function extractBlocks(msg: AIMessage) {
  const reasoningBlocks = msg.contentBlocks
    .filter((b) => b.type === "reasoning")
    .map((b) => b.reasoning);

  const textBlocks = msg.contentBlocks
    .filter((b) => b.type === "text")
    .map((b) => b.text);

  return {
    reasoning: reasoningBlocks.join(""),
    text: textBlocks.join(""),
  };
}
```
This function takes an `AIMessage` as input and returns an object with two properties: `reasoning` and `text`. The `reasoning` property is a string that contains the joined reasoning blocks, while the `text` property is a string that contains the joined text blocks.

Note that this function assumes that the `contentBlocks` array on the `AIMessage` contains both reasoning and text blocks. If your message only contains one type of block, you may need to modify the function accordingly.

